---
title: add_to_bloom (osaka-bloom)
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> q_init : start
    q_init --> q_hash : hashed = keccak256(bloom_entry)
    q_hash --> q_iter : idx = 0
    q_iter --> q_extract : idx in (0, 2, 4)
    q_extract --> q_bit_set : bit_to_set = Uint.from_be_bytes(hashed[idx:idx+2]) AND 0x07FF
    q_bit_set --> q_bit_index : bit_index = 0x07FF - int(bit_to_set)
    q_bit_index --> q_byte_index : byte_index = bit_index // 8
    q_byte_index --> q_bit_value : bit_value = 1 << (7 - (bit_index % 8))
    q_bit_value --> q_update : bloom[byte_index] = bloom[byte_index] | bit_value
    q_update --> q_iter : idx = next(idx)
    q_iter --> q_final : idx exhausted
    q_final --> [*] : done

    note right of q_extract
        INV: bit_to_set is always in range [0, 2047]
        (11-bit mask 0x07FF)
    end note

    note right of q_byte_index
        INV: byte_index is always in range [0, 255]
    end note

    note right of q_iter
        INV: The loop iterates exactly 3 times
        (indices 0, 2, 4), setting 3 bits per bloom entry
    end note

    note right of q_init
        INV: bloom bytearray must be exactly 256 bytes.
        keccak256 output is at least 6 bytes to support
        3 pairs of 2-byte reads.
    end note
